Date: Sun 19 Jun 2011
Source: IBNLive, Press Trust of India (PTI) report [edited]
http://ibnlive.in.com/generalnewsfeed/news/man-dies-of-suspected-anthrax/730731.html


Man dies of suspected anthrax
-----------------------------
One person from Kandhamal district who was undergoing treatment for
suspected anthrax, died at a hospital [in Berhampur, Orissa], official
sources said today [19 Jun 2011]. The deceased ... of Bada Guchhuka
village in Kandhamal died at the MKCG Medical College Hospital [in
Berhampur] last night, Kandhamal CDMO [chief district medical officer]
NC Behera said.

While Majhi along with 6 others were admitted in the hospital last
week [week of 13 Jun 2011] after suffering from suspected anthrax, and
8 people, including a 4 year old girl, were admitted to the hospital
in the 2nd phase. All the 14 patients belonged to San Guchhuka and
Bada Guchhuka villages of Tumudibandh block, he said. While 2 of them
were completely cured, the condition of others is improving", the CDMO
said.

Besides the 2 villages, the disease had not spread to other places
following precautionary measures to contain its spread, Behera added.

